      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum finite element representation with nonlinear contact and bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity captures the dominant physics of compression-bending response.",
      "rationale": "The model employs 3-D continuum elements with frictional contact (mu=0.3) at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces, and bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity for Ti-6Al-4V ELI. Geometric nonlinearity enabled. Model form is consistent with published literature for implant compression-bending simulation and with FDA-validated FEA frameworks for ASTM F1717."
