    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three primary QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) satisfy pre-established acceptance criteria. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 static protocol is the regulatory standard and the primary decision question does not require cyclic or combined loading validation at this stage. The material property dataset predating the February 2026 model revision is noted; re-validation of model inputs against the revised geometry is planned for Q2 2026 and will be documented in a subsequent credibility assessment update.",
